  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The main element creates a main landmark for screen reader navigation</li>
      <li>Only one visible main element per page (others must have <code>hidden</code> attribute)</li>
      <li>Skip links should target the main element: <code>&lt;a href="#main"&gt;Skip to content&lt;/a&gt;</code></li>
      <li>Add <code>id="main"</code> and optionally <code>tabindex="-1"</code> to receive focus from skip links</li>
      <li>Main should not be nested inside article, aside, footer, header, or nav</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

